416
00:44:44,440 --> 00:44:46,249
XANDER: Aren't they fun?
Excuse me?

417
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:48,767
You know who that is?
It's John du Pont.

418
00:44:49,320 --> 00:44:52,130
- I said hi, Mark.
- MARK: It's John du Pont.

419
00:44:52,280 --> 00:44:56,046
The most generous man in America. You
can't treat him like he's anyone.

420
00:44:56,200 --> 00:44:58,851
DAVE: Mark, she said hi.
Mark, I said hi, okay?

421
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:01,367
DANI: She said hi. You
said hi from over there.

422
00:45:01,520 --> 00:45:02,726
Buddy. Mark.

423
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:05,565
- She said hi, pal.
- NANCY: Mark.

424
00:45:05,760 --> 00:45:08,764
- You're in our room.
- MARK: I'm in your room? Okay. All right.

425
00:45:08,920 --> 00:45:11,161
Great. You know what?
You don't even know.

426
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:14,210
You don't even know what you don't know.
You know that?

427
00:45:14,360 --> 00:45:15,486
NANCY: Dave? Dad.

428
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:18,007
Mark. Why? Dad.

429
00:45:18,160 --> 00:45:19,730
- DANI: No.
- NANCY: Yes.

430
00:45:19,880 --> 00:45:22,406
- XANDER: Dad.
- DAVE: Buddy.

431
00:45:22,560 --> 00:45:23,925
Mark.

432
00:45:25,680 --> 00:45:28,490
Buddy. Come here.

433
00:45:29,920 --> 00:45:31,410
Come here.

434
00:45:32,280 --> 00:45:35,011
Give me the tape. Okay.

435
00:45:35,160 --> 00:45:40,041
Nanev can't set up his arm spin
without setting up himself.

436
00:45:40,200 --> 00:45:44,046
You just hit yours first. When
you feel him drive, hit it.

437
00:45:44,840 --> 00:45:45,921
All right?

438
00:45:46,080 --> 00:45:48,765
He's gonna drive
and turn you and...

439
00:45:49,360 --> 00:45:51,010
DAVE: There it is.

440
00:45:52,000 --> 00:45:54,685
That's it. Drive him out.
Drive him out.

441
00:45:54,840 --> 00:45:56,251
Drive him.

442
00:45:56,440 --> 00:45:58,522
Drive, drive!

443
00:45:59,880 --> 00:46:01,405
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

444
00:46:01,600 --> 00:46:03,762
(APPLAUSE)

445
00:46:15,080 --> 00:46:17,970
(INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE)

446
00:46:19,400 --> 00:46:22,324
<i>(MUSIC)</i>

447
00:46:35,760 --> 00:46:37,000
(CROWD CHEERING)

448
00:46:37,560 --> 00:46:40,803
DAVE: Elbows deep, Mark.
Drive! Drive!

449
00:46:41,600 --> 00:46:42,806
Five seconds, Mark!

450
00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:45,209
Drive him. That's it.

451
00:46:45,400 --> 00:46:48,085
Drive him, drive him, drive him!
Pop him up!

452
00:46:49,160 --> 00:46:51,162
Yeah!

453
00:46:51,320 --> 00:46:52,924
That's it, buddy!

454
00:46:53,120 --> 00:46:55,646
Yeah! Yeah!

455
00:46:58,120 --> 00:47:03,001
CROWD CHANTING: <i>U.S.A.!
U.S.A.! U.S.A.!</i>

456
00:47:06,760 --> 00:47:08,922
(CROWD CHEERING)

457
00:47:18,600 --> 00:47:21,649
(DAVID BOWIE'S "FAME" PLAYING)

458
00:47:28,840 --> 00:47:31,491
JOHN: Oh, there we go.

459
00:47:35,720 --> 00:47:37,643
Who needs a refill?

460
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:43,480
Let's all get very drunk.

461
00:47:47,440 --> 00:47:50,364
MAN: Can I take a look at your medal?
Yeah. Yeah.

462
00:47:55,280 --> 00:47:57,521
What a fantastic evening.

463
00:47:58,520 --> 00:48:02,764
<i>♪ Fame, makes a man ♪
♪ Take things over ♪</i>

464
00:48:03,560 --> 00:48:07,770
<i>♪ Fame, lets him loose ♪
♪ Hard to swallow ♪</i>

465
00:48:08,640 --> 00:48:13,009
<i>♪ Fame, puts you there ♪
♪ Where things are hollow ♪</i>

466
00:48:13,840 --> 00:48:15,524
<i>♪ Fame ♪</i>

467
00:48:18,880 --> 00:48:20,689
<i>♪ Fame, it's not your brain ♪</i>

468
00:48:20,840 --> 00:48:23,605
JOHN: All right. All right.

469
00:48:24,040 --> 00:48:26,361
Enough. Enough!

470
00:48:26,520 --> 00:48:28,045
Turn that off.

471
00:48:29,320 --> 00:48:30,481
Take that down.

472
00:48:30,640 --> 00:48:31,721
(MUSIC STOPS)

473
00:48:31,880 --> 00:48:34,360
- MAN 1: Where do you want me to put it?
- JOHN: I don't care.

474
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:37,000
Throw it away.

475
00:48:39,800 --> 00:48:43,009
All of it, whole shelf.

476
00:48:53,880 --> 00:48:56,201
Horses are stupid.

477
00:48:59,120 --> 00:49:01,521
Horses eat and shit.

478
00:49:02,200 --> 00:49:04,123
That's all they do.

479
00:49:05,920 --> 00:49:07,524
(LAUGHS)

480
00:49:08,600 --> 00:49:10,602
It's very silly.

481
00:49:11,920 --> 00:49:14,127
It's all very silly.

482
00:49:18,120 --> 00:49:21,408
<i>Hove my mother very
much, but she...</i>

483
00:49:23,520 --> 00:49:24,851
She... It's...

484
00:49:27,120 --> 00:49:29,009
It's ridiculous.

485
00:49:30,560 --> 00:49:33,245
Sitting on an animal
